<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3278] CRON scheduling does not work correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3278</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a listener with an event handler listening for messages and logging when they come in.&lt;br/&gt;
I sent a message to that queue with CRON string of &quot;25 * * * *&quot;.  All other scheduler properties are not set.  No ttl.&lt;br/&gt;
The first time 25 after the hour comes around, a message is sent and my listener receives it.&lt;br/&gt;
All subsequent times 25 after the hour come around, the listener doesn&apos;t receive anything.&lt;br/&gt;
The admin console Queues page shows that the subsequent messages are waiting in the queue but drilling into the queue shows no message.&lt;br/&gt;
Restarting ActiveMQ and the Queues page doesn&apos;t show any messages.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 7&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
